name: Client service access rights subjects search filter clearing restore initial state

steps.name: Given SecurityServer login page is open
And Page is prepared to be tested
And User xrd logs in to SecurityServer with password secret
And Service with code "testOp1" is opened
And Service add subjects dialog is opened
When Click Search button on subject dialog
Then The query return 9 entries in the subjects table
When Adding value for member name, member code, subsystem and then click the remove value button on the input field
$("By.xpath: //div[@data-test='name-text-field']/By.xpath: .//input") should be(empty: attribute value="" and exact text "")
$("By.xpath: //div[@data-test='name-text-field']/By.xpath: .//input") should be(empty: attribute value="" and exact text "")
$("By.xpath: //div[@data-test='member-code-text-field']/By.xpath: .//input") should be(empty: attribute value="" and exact text "")
$("By.xpath: //div[@data-test='member-code-text-field']/By.xpath: .//input") should be(empty: attribute value="" and exact text "")
$("By.xpath: //div[@data-test='subsystem-code-text-field']/By.xpath: .//input") should be(empty: attribute value="" and exact text "")
$("By.xpath: //div[@data-test='subsystem-code-text-field']/By.xpath: .//input") should be(empty: attribute value="" and exact text "")
And Click Search button on subject dialog
Then The query return 9 entries in the subjects table
